  "description": "Very large, plump warbler. Full eyering is mostly white, but buff tan/yellow in front area above upper mandible.\u00a0 Large, bi-colored bill, with darker upper mandible and lighter lower mandible.\u00a0 Tannish-Brown hood, much lighter buff/tan throat.\u00a0 Breast and Belly bright yellow.\u00a0 Olive-gray back and upperparts.\u00a0 Wings more gray with olive edging.\u00a0 No subloral line.\u00a0 \u00a0UTC reach more than half way to tip of tail, creating appearance of short tail.\u00a0 Caught in mist net #6 on 8:10am net run at Bird Conservancy of the Rockies Barr Lake State Park Banding Station.",
